                            <comment id="156628" author="yong.fan" created="Thu, 23 Jun 2016 04:35:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After the painful debugging from millions of lines logs, I found that the failure should related with the following scenario:&lt;br/&gt;
1) The client sent unlink (PFID/test1) RPC to the MDT1;&lt;br/&gt;
2) The MDT0 failover;&lt;br/&gt;
3) The MDT1 is replaying with the MDT0;&lt;br/&gt;
4) At that time, the step 1) trigger lookup(test1) RPC from the MDT1 to the MDT0 for the test1&apos;s FID.&lt;br/&gt;
5) But because the MDT0 recovery is not completed yet, the test1&apos;s FID on the MDT0 is still the old one. That means the MDT0 reply the MDT1 with an invalid test1&apos;s FID.&lt;br/&gt;
6) The MDT1 uses the MDT0 given test1&apos;s FID to locate the target child object to be deleted, found nothing. Then the unlink operation failed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
